			<abstract>
				<p>Testimony of Anzelm Landesmann regarding his wounding during the deportation of Jews from Skalat, his escape together with his
					brother from a transport to Belzec, after which they parted, his work on a farm until 1944, when the area was liberated by the Red
					Army, and his return to Skalat.</p>
			</abstract>
