	<text>
		<body>
			<p><persName ref="#ehri_et_landesman_anzelm">Anzelm Landesmann</persName> Testimony (doc. 301/905)</p>
			<p>Typescript, 1 page, 210 x 295 mm, Polish language</p>

			<p><pb n="1" facs="EHRI-ET-ZIH3011713_01.jpg"/>
				<persName ref="#ehri_et_landesman_anzelm">Anzelm Landesmann</persName>. Twelve years old. He comes from <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/693700/skalat.html">Skałat</placeName>. He has two brothers, one is a corporal in the Polish <term
					type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1076">Army</term> and the other, 17 years old, was baptized
				and stayed with the <term type="subject" ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_ukrainians">Ukrainians</term> in the vicinity of <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/693700/skalat.html">Skałat</placeName>. <persName ref="#ehri_et_landesman_anzelm">Anzelm</persName>,
				called <persName ref="#ehri_et_landesman_anzelm">Jaśko</persName> by the <term type="subject" ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_ukrainians"
					>Ukrainians</term>, arrived in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3099230/gliwice.html">Gliwice</placeName> with the
				transport of <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1226">repatriates</term> and was sent to the
					<term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824">Children</term>’s Home in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/3101619/chorzow.html">Chorzów</placeName>.</p>

			<p><persName ref="#ehri_et_landesman_anzelm">Janek</persName> recounts:</p>
			<p>There were seven <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824">children</term> in our [family]. I
				got up in the morning. The <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-550" type="subject">action</term>. I <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204" type="subject">ran away</term> this way, Mom that way, younger
				brother this way. When I was <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204" type="subject">running away</term> a
					<term type="subject" ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">German</term> shot after me, he wounded me in the head. I fell. They
				thought I was dead and everybody trampled on me, I didn’t even gasp and was just lying. The <term type="subject"
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term> left, I got up and went to the <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-282">hospital</term> where they bandaged my head. I returned home, parents
				were no more and I was with a farmer I knew. Then the <term type="subject" ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term> came
				again, caught me [and took me] to the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-758" type="subject"
					>synagogue</term> and [loaded me] onto a truck and [took me] to <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/691650/ternopil.html"
					>Tarnopol</placeName>. From <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/691650/ternopil.html">Tarnopol</placeName> everyone was <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-115" type="subject">deported</term> to <placeName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-41" type="camp">Bełżec</placeName>. My sister <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204" type="subject">escaped</term> from the truck and fell shot by a
				bullet. She <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204" type="subject">ran away</term> during the day, that’s
				why she didn’t make it, that’s why my brother and I <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204" type="subject"
					>escaped</term> in the evening. A <term type="subject" ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">German</term> fired, wounded my
				brother in the leg and myself in the face (<persName ref="#ehri_et_landesman_anzelm">Janek</persName> was wounded twice, in the head
				and in the face). But we did manage to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204" type="subject">escape</term>
				and we walked at night only. What to do…? We split, my brother went in one direction, I in the other. I went to the countryside and
				entered a house. There was only a <term type="subject" ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_ukrainians">Ukrainian</term> couple, I told them
				that I was from <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/709611/drohobych.html">Drohobycz</placeName>, that there is <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204" type="subject">hunger</term> there and that I worked there. But I
				told them that I wanted to work here. They were glad that I would herd cows. I spoke good Ukrainian because at home I used to play
				with the neighbors’ <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824">children</term>. I knew how to
				pray in Polish and in Ukrainian. I worked for them, I forgot Yiddish but sometimes I wanted to say something in Yiddish to a horse in
				the stable but something would block my throat and wouldn’t let me. A village head came and asked for the names of my father and
				mother. I said: Michał and Natusia [Nastusia]. I made up names for my grandpa and grandma. Once, I was herding cows and I heard
				someone singing, a familiar voice.<note place="bottom">Anzelm Landesmann used a Ukrainian word for ‘voice.’</note> I run to the road,
				I look, it’s my younger brother, I raised my hand, I weep, shout, he stopped, climbed down the cart, he wept too. Then he drove on and
				I never saw my brother again. I worked like this until the winter of <date when="1944">1944</date>. Then the <orgName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-004583">Soviets</orgName> came and I thought there were no Jews left but I
				went to <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/693700/skalat.html">Skałat</placeName> to see our house, I look and my uncle is
				walking down the street and he brought me to <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3099230/gliwice.html">Gliwice</placeName>.</p>
			<p>Record taken by <persName ref="#ehri_et_gliksztejn_ida">Gliksztejn Ida</persName>. <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/3101950/bytom.html">Bytom</placeName>.</p>
